President Muhammadu Buhari has commiserated with the Sani Abacha’s family over the death of their son, Abdullahi, on Saturday. In a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu, the President prayed for the repose of Abdullahi. “President Muhammadu Buhari extends heartfelt condolences to the former First Lady, Marayam Abacha, and family on the death of their son, Abdullahi. Read Also: Burna Boy mourns AKA, says I told him to buy gun “The President’s prayers and thoughts are with the family of Abacha as they grieve the passing of the young Abdullahi. “The President prays for the repose of the soul of the deceased and comfort for those who mourn,” the statement reads.